      <title>工党获胜后英国商业信心和订单增长</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-07-24/uk-business-confidence-and-orders-grow-after-labour-election-win</link>
      <description><![CDATA[英国工党在选举中取得压倒性胜利后，英国私营企业信心、招聘和新订单均大幅增加，这表明新政府可能带来更强劲的增长势头。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-07-24/uk-business-confidence-and-orders-grow-after-labour-election-win</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 24 Jul 2024 08:30:00 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>南非通胀率因食品价格放缓至六个月低点</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-07-24/south-african-inflation-slows-as-food-and-transport-costs-cool</link>
      <description><![CDATA[南非 6 月份通胀率小幅下降，触及六个月低点，这可能促使央行考虑在今年晚些时候削减借贷成本。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-07-24/south-african-inflation-slows-as-food-and-transport-costs-cool</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 24 Jul 2024 08:12:25 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>盈利疲软并非投资者的“恐慌时刻”：L&G</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/2024-07-24/earnings-weakness-not-panic-moment-for-investors-l-g-video</link>
      <description><![CDATA[Legal &amp; General Investment Management 首席投资官 Sonja Laud 表示，美国和欧洲许多公司的盈利疲软并不代表“恐慌时刻”。 Laud 在彭博电视台发表讲话时表示，市场反应“非常正常，应该预料到”，并补充说，分析师和投资者将关注这些公司中大多数公司的“可重复和可持续的盈利状况”。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/2024-07-24/earnings-weakness-not-panic-moment-for-investors-l-g-video</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 24 Jul 2024 08:10:19 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
